Conclusion 
-
my understanding of what hacking is could be digital and analogue.
if something has a system it can definitely be hacked. 
hacking is for me inspecting its system, disecting it, understand how something works, add or change something to its system with the outcome of something new.
hacking something does not necessarily need an outcome that have to be real, it could also be in my perception something autonomous for example what i learned from Joseph's workshop.
the hacking method that i found interesting is combining things together, finding a combinations that could colide, interact and become someting one. 
-
Nanco Speur, 0940509.
